name: market for operation, intermodal shipping container | operation, intermodal shipping container | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/13889/documentation

This is a market activity. Each market represents the consumption mix of a product in a given geography, connecting suppliers with consumers of the same product in the same geographical area. Markets group the producers and also the imports of the product (if relevant) within the same geographical area. They also account for transport to the consumer and for the losses during that process, when relevant.;This is the market for  'operation, intermodal shipping container', in the Global geography.;Transport from producers to consumers of this product in the geography covered by the market is included.;The 'operation, intermodal shipping container' is delivering the service of operation of a intermodal shipping container that is used to store 1kg of cargo for 1 day. The container has a lifetime of 15 years and a TEU (Twenty-foot Equivalent Unit) of 1-2. The service also includes the needed maintenance.

This activity starts with the service generation.


This activity ends with the service supplied to its consumers. Transport or losses are considered irrelevant for this product.
